Package: jiopc-testing-agent
Version: @VERSION@
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-yaml, python3-psutil
Recommends: python3-venv, python3-pip
Maintainer: InnovAstra <developer@moxiebeauty.in>
Homepage: https://example.com/jiopc-testing-agent
Description: JioPC image validation agent (web, native, desktop presence)
 Scripted validation agent for freshly patched JioPC OS images:
 web apps reachable and visually sound (Part A, Playwright),
 native apps healthy (Part B, psutil), desktop folders and
 start-menu categories correct (Part C). Writes a JSONL log to
 ~/.local/share/jiopc/agent/ and ships a model-agnostic LLM
 analysis layer (jiopc-agent-analyse). Root is used only at
 install time; runtime is pure user-space.
 .
 Playwright/Chromium for Part A cannot come from apt; postinst
 sets up /opt/jiopc-testing-agent/venv best-effort. If that step
 fails the package still installs and Parts B/C work; Part A then
 logs ERROR records with the manual install hint (see INSTALL.md).
